                            <h1>Sowmya Kashi</h1>
                            <p>Sowmya Kashi, hailing from Sagara Taluk, Karnataka, has been captivated by Kannada
                                Literature since her early years. Influenced by literary giants like SL Bhyrappa, Ravi
                                Belegere, Yendamoori Veerendranath, and Poornachandra Tejasvi,
                                she began penning down her thoughts in the form of poetry during high school. With over
                                100 poems to her credit, Sowmya pursued her passion further by earning a Master's degree
                                in Journalism from Jain University,
                                Bengaluru. Her literary impact has been felt by a wide audience, with her poetry, in
                                particular, reaching over 1 Million people through
                                platforms like Instagram Reels. Notably, she authored the book "Helade Ulidaddu," a
                                collection of small poetries that has achieved considerable success, having sold more
                                than 1000 copies.
                                Sowmya Kashi aspires to kindle a love for Kannada literature among the youth and
